<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
A rare species generally found in disturbed habitats, especially on disturbed soil and concrete, and possibly introduced from the northern hemisphere. There is only one record from Chile in disturbed habitats in the capitol Santiago (
<bibRefCitation author="Ochi, H" journalOrPublisher="Hikobia" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="221 - 223" refId="B19" refString="Ochi, H, Mahu, M, 1988. Supplement to the Bryoideae (Bryaceae, Musci) in South America. Hikobia 10: 221 - 223" title="Supplement to the Bryoideae (Bryaceae, Musci) in South America." volume="10" year="1988">Ochi and Mahu 1988</bibRefCitation>
, at HO, not seen!). It is characterized by its dioicous sexual condition, rosulate to somewhat evenly foliate stems, small leaves that are irregularly contorted when dry, costa excurrent into a medium-length awn, a narrow but usually distinct limbidium, and serrulate distal leaf margins. The plants are often reddish-tinged. The rhizoidal tubers are diagnostic; predominantly red, with strongly protuberant cell walls, from 100-280 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, often arising from lower leaf axils or at the base of the stem on short rhizoids. The species has a scattered world-wide temperate distribution (Illustrations: 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1179/006813864804812128" author="Crundwell, AC" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Bryological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="597 - 637" refId="B2" refString="Crundwell, AC, Nyholm, E, 1964. The European species of the Bryum erythrocarpum complex. Transactions of the British Bryological Society 4 (4): 597 - 637, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1179/006813864804812128" title="The European species of the Bryum erythrocarpum complex." url="https://doi.org/10.1179/006813864804812128" volume="4" year="1964">Crundwell and Nyholm 1964</bibRefCitation>
: 630, as 
